# 10. 星は何度でも

Ichika: (Now that I know I'm writing a song to show them all my support, it's become so much easier to come up with the melody and lyrics for it.)
Ichika: (I also know which feelings to channel into it.)
Classmate: Huh? Aren't you gonna go buy lunch, Hoshino...?
Ichika: No, I have to take care of something else first.
Ichika: This part feels a little sad and lonely. I'm trying to show support, so it needs to feel more optimistic.
Ichika: Hmm... This isn't right.
Ichika: (Seeing them all work hard has allowed me to finally take a big step forward. That's why I want to help them do the same...)
Ichika: (The more they pursue their own goals, the less we'll get to see each other.)
Ichika: (But...)
Ichika: “As long as our hearts are one”...
Ichika: No, just “our hearts are one”... That should also make Miku smile when she sings it.
Ichika: This is coming along nicely...
Ichika: Oh, I know. I should try having Miku sing it now.
Miku: ♪—— ♪————...
Ichika: ...! This is much closer to what I've been envisioning!
Ichika: I like this melody, so I could try throwing in a few extra sounds to give it more volume.
Ichika: (I want this song to guide them.)
Ichika: (So they can reach the places they want to go without ever getting lost.)
Ichika: (No matter how far apart we are, we'll always be together.)
Ichika: (And Miku's going to deliver that message.)
Ichika: It's finished...
Ichika: I did it! My song for Saki and the others is done...
Ichika: It's finally... *Yawn*
Ichika: I'm a little sleep-deprived, but I managed to finish it in time for the meteor shower...
Ichika: What time is it...? Okay, good. It started raining when it got dark, but how's the weather now?
Ichika: Oh...
Ichika: It's still cloudy. I can't see anything.
Ichika: (I was hoping to have them listen to it while watching the meteor shower since we can't do that together...)
Ichika: But I finished writing my song, so I should send it to them.
Ichika: (Miku...)
Ichika: (Thank you for bearing with me all this time. I wouldn't have been able to complete this song without you.)
Ichika: (Please take my feelings, and deliver them to Saki and the others through the song we made together...)
Ichika: Okay, it's sent...
Ichika: I'm starting to feel really nervous for some reason...
Ichika: ...
Ichika: I think I'll go take a quick walk.
Junior Club Members: Great job today, Tenma!
Saki: You guys also did awesome! Get home safe, okay?!
Saki: (That trip we took today was so much fun. Not only did I learn a lot, I even got to become friends with the girls over there.)
Saki: I hope we get to go back... *Yawn* So sleepy. Even though I slept a ton on the bus ride back...
Saki: (It's already past seven... I know it's a little early, but I might take a bath and go straight to bed when I get home.)
Saki: Oh, wait, the meteor shower...! Isn't right now the best time to watch?
Saki: It's too cloudy! I can't see anything...!
Saki: *Sigh*
Saki: (I wonder if Ichi and the others are trying to watch it right now too.)
Saki: Hm? A message from Ichi...?
Saki: This is...!
Honami: (I really enjoyed that open house. I got to hear so much about life on campus from those current students.)
Honami: (But it seems too far for me to commute each day. If I'm going to attend that university, then I may want to live somewhere nearby.)
Honami: (All by myself...)
Honami: The sky's so cloudy... And the ground's wet. It must've rained earlier.
Honami: ...
Honami: I wish I could've seen the meteor shower...
Honami: (Not only that...)
Honami: Huh? A message...?
Honami: It's finished...?!
Iori: Anyway, see you tomorrow.
Shiho: Okay, see you tomorrow.
Shiho: (We finished checking over those songs a lot quicker than I was initially expecting.)
Shiho: (To be fair, today's songs were the ones we regularly play during our shows.)
Shiho: Come to think of it, I wonder what's going on with the Leonid meteor shower...
Shiho: Hmm... I can't really see anything. It's too cloudy...
Shiho: (Also, there's no point in looking at it by myself...)
Shiho: I should get home and practice...
Shiho: Oh, Ichika sent something...
Ichika's Message: <I wrote a song to show my support for the three of you, and I had Miku sing it. I hope you get a chance to listen to it.>
Shiho: (Yeah, she did say she was working on a Miku song.)
Shiho: A song to support us? What's it like?
Miku: <♪—— ♪————>
Shiho: ...!
Shiho: (Wait, this sensation...)
Miku: <♪—— ♪————>
Honami: (Miku's voice is so gentle.)
Honami: (It's like she's saying, “I'm right here,” and, “Let's go together,” while holding my hand.)
Miku: <♪—— ♪——...>
Saki: (The lyrics are also really good...)
Saki: (She's reassuring me that even if things get tough, she'll be there for me. That I'm not alone.)
Saki: (But...)
Shiho: (For some reason, while listening to this song...)
Shiho: (My heart's starting to sink a bit.)
Ichika: Saki and Honami won't be joining us, so we can try doing this again another time...
Ichika: I'm really sorry, you two...! Please forget what we just said.
Ichika: I think you should also prioritize your own dream, Honami.
Honami: (Why...?)
Honami: (Why am I getting the feeling that Ichika's incredibly lonely?)
Honami: That must be it...
Honami: Ichika probably...
Saki: She hid how lonely she really was in order to write this song for us.
Shiho: It's a bit unrefined, but it's also a great expression of who Ichika is...
Shiho: Hm? A message from Saki...?
Saki's Message: <Can I call you, Ichi? I wanna talk about your song.>
Honami: (Saki also listened to it already.)
Ichika's Message: <I'm outside, but now should be fine since there's nobody else around.>
Saki's Message: <Were you at work? If we can talk in person, then I wanna do that!>
Ichika's Message: <No, I wasn't working. I was about to go to the park. I couldn't stay still after sending that song to all of you.>
Shiho: The park...?
Ichika: (Saki hasn't replied. What's going on...?)
???: Ichiii!
Ichika: Huh...?
Ichika: Saki?! Honami? Shiho? But why...?
Saki: Hehe. I just told you that I wanted to talk to you in person, didn't I?
Shiho: We felt the same way. After seeing your message, we knew that this is where you'd be.
Saki: Thanks for writing that song for us, Ichi. It made me really happy, and cheered me up so much.
Ichika: R-Really...?
Honami: The same goes for me... I actually started tearing up a little.
Shiho: We understand exactly how you feel now. Which is pretty amazing considering it was your very first song.
Ichika: ...!
Ichika: Really...? Thank goodness.
Saki: Also, Ichi...
Saki: I'm really sorry!!
Ichika: Huh?
Saki: I was totally focused on myself. I never thought about how you were feeling, Ichi.
Saki: That includes today. I told you that I had to go with my club instead of watching the meteor shower with you...
Saki: Instead of flat out refusing your invitation, I could've offered to call you while looking up at the sky or join you later in the evening.
Ichika: Thanks, Saki... But I didn't want you to...
Saki: No, I should've done more!
Saki: I've been wanting to hang out and spend more time together, but I didn't do anything to make that happen.
Saki: I kept relying on the idea that you'd let me do what I want. That you'd all understand...
Ichika: Saki...
Honami: I also deserve some of the blame. I should've done more, and I'm incredibly sorry...
Shiho: Me too. I'm so sorry, Ichika, Saki, Honami.
Ichika: No... You were all just doing your best to...
Shiho: That isn't an excuse to leave a friend hanging.
Shiho: Especially when they're feeling lonely. Especially when that friend is forcing herself to be our cheerleader.
Ichika: Oh...
Honami: I also got that sense from your song, Ichika. I understand your true feelings now.
Honami: Which means you must've spent quite a lot of effort channeling your feelings into this song.
Ichika: I did my best to keep those lonely thoughts out of it since I was trying to support all of you.
Saki: No, you made your support crystal clear.
Saki: But... Even if you were able to cheer us up, you'd still be lonely.
Ichika: Oh...
Shiho: Things would end with us being cheered up, and that doesn't feel right.
Honami: Yes, and...
Honami: I really want us to create another memory together.
Honami: A precious memory that we can only create together right this moment.
Saki: So, Ichi!
Saki: Let us know if there's anything you wanna do! We can do it together!
Ichika: Anything I want to do...?
Ichika: So, I was planning on singing the song I sent to all of you at the school festival...
Ichika: Some girls are going to be performing as a band, so I was thinking about asking them to play for me.
Saki: What?! You're gonna be in a band, Ichi?!
Ichika: Not exactly... More like collaborate with them. They'll play their instruments while I sing.
Honami: Did you already ask them, Ichika?
Ichika: Not yet. My plan was to ask them after I'd finished working on my song...
Shiho: In that case, don't ask them.
Saki: Yeah! We should be the ones playing your song!
Ichika: Wait, does that mean...?
Honami: Would you be okay with us performing it?
Ichika: Are you sure...?
Ichika: But you're all so busy...
Honami: I've become much better at writing essays, so I'll ask them to reduce the number of assignments I need to do until the school festival.
Saki: I also promise to make time for practice! I can stop practicing by myself during lunch, and keep my schedule open on weekends after club gets out!
Shiho: Sorry, I have to stay focused on my band's show since it's happening next week.
Shiho: But things should settle down soon after, so I'll probably have time to practice.
Shiho: However, if we are gonna do this, we're not cutting any corners. Are you okay with that...?
Ichika: Yes...!
Ichika: Let's play it together!
Shiho: Now, have you already applied to perform?
Ichika: Yeah, but I've only told them that I'd be singing a song...
Ichika: The festival committee member in my class told me to have the details hammered out by next week.
Saki: Then, we gotta tell her that the four of us are gonna perform as a band♪
Honami: Also, since we're going to be participating as a group, we'll need to come up with a name for ourselves.
Shiho: A name?
Honami: Yes. In our case, a band name.
Saki: Right! Then...
Saki: I know! What about “The Ichikas”? She's the reason why we're doing this, and we'll be performing her song!
Shiho: That's so lame...
Ichika: Sorry, that'd also be kind of embarrassing for me...
Saki: But!
Ichika: What should we call ourselves...?
Saki: Hmm... Oh, hold on!
Ichika: Did you get another lightbulb?
Shiho: I hope it's not another lame name.
Saki: You're so mean, Shiho! Anyway, it's not that...!
Saki: Look! Up at the sky!
Ichika: Huh?
Honami: Oh, it's clear now...!
Shiho: But it was really cloudy just a second ago.
Ichika: Oh, over there! I just saw a shooting star!
Honami: Me too! Oh, there's another one!
Saki: This is so cool! They're everywhere! Are you watching, Shiho?!
Shiho: Yes, I'm watching. Try to relax.
Ichika: They're so beautiful...
Honami: We finally got to see it together again...
Ichika: Yeah.
Ichika: About our band name...
Ichika: Why don't we go with something that really suits us?
Shiho: Then, a constellation...? We are looking at the Leonid meteor shower right now.
Saki: Yeah! Look at Shiho on a sentimental streak♪
Shiho: There you go, poking fun at me again.
Shiho: (Hang on. Just now...)
Saki: What's this meteor shower called in other languages...?
Honami: I'll check. Let's see...
Honami: In English, this is the Leonid meteor shower. And in French, they're called “Les Léonides”...
Ichika: Léonides...? That has a nice ring to it.
Saki: It even has the word “need” in it! Like the way we all need each other♪
Saki: Huh...?
Saki: Didn't we have this same conversation somewhere else before...?
Shiho: Yeah, I was just thinking the same thing.
Shiho: Next, Ichika's supposed to...
Ichika: Spell out the name of our band! One second...
Ichika: It's this, right...?
Honami: “Leoneed”...?
Honami: Yes, that's right! Then, Saki, you...
Saki: Throw in a shooting star in the form of a slash! Like this!
Ichika: “Leo/need”...
Ichika: That's right...
Ichika: We're...
Shiho: How did we forget...?
Shiho: Forget about something this important...?
Saki: We've been doing all sorts of stuff as a band for like ever now!
Saki: We've done a ton of shows, and even produced our own songs!
Honami: That's right. The four of us decided to go pro together in order to move the hearts of as many people as we could through our music...!
Honami: And we've been blessed enough to perform at some incredibly large venues!
Ichika: That means...
Ichika: Moving forward...
Ichika: The four of us get to keep being in a band together.
